items.title: Dow posts record high close; S&P 500, Nasdaq end down
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 137.89 points, or 0.33%, to 42,313.00, the S&P 500 fell 7.20 points, or 0.13%, to 5,738.17 and the Nasdaq Composite fell 70.70 points, or 0.39%, to 18,119.59.

items.title: 48 smallcaps give double-digit gain as broader indices climb to fresh high
items.description: The near-term uptrend of the market remains intact. Nifty could eventually bounce after the consolidation in the next few sessions. Immediate support is at 25900, says Nagaraj Shetti, Senior Technical Research Analyst at HDFC Securities.

items.title: Market continues record run in second week; all sectors gain
items.description: The Indian rupee closed 13 paise lower at 83.70 on September 27 against its September 20 closing of 83.57.

items.title: PTC Industries stock jumps 2% on BAE Systems' deal to supply titanium castings for M777 Howitzer
items.description: The lightweight titanium castings for the 155mm M777 ULH will be produced at PTC Industries' state-of-the-art production facility in Lucknow
